item.title: Jagex is going hard :L
item.dc:creator: @Frell Frell
item.description:
@Frell wrote:

Davidi2:

When you create something like that, unless you have a developer really skilled in their design you are going to end up with spaghetti code. It’s a bit sad that they don’t even feel confident enough to go through and clean it up, or maybe they dont have the manpower (or care enough), but it really isn’t a good sign for the team.

Ian Gower said on a livestream they’ve been doing this from the start, they get ahead of themselves looking forward and that’s why they have so many broken things in the game.

One of the content developers said when they wrote summoning Runescript didn’t have the “&&” operator so it was a mess hardcoding all of the specific cases.
